This paper deals with privacy-preserving data mining, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses optimization techniques to improve the efficiency of the mining process, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the use of distortion parameters, which is a concept from information theory (cs.IT).
